EVENT HANDLING
- java.awt.event.*;
- EVENT ~ An event is an object that describes a change of state in a source, it can be generated as a consequences of a person interacting with the elements in a 
Graphical user interface (GUI)
- EVENT SOURCES ~ A source is an object that generates an event. This occurs when the interval state of that object changes in someway.
- Public void addtypelistener (typelistener object)
- EVENT LISTENERS ~ A listener is an object that is notified when an event occurs.
        - It has two important requirements.
            1. It must have been registered with one or more sources to receive notifications about specific type of events.
            2. 
